-05-01 10:25:58','2019-05-01 08:25:58','','Home','','publish','closed','closed','','home','','','2019-05-01 10:30:51','2019-05-01 08:30:51','',0,'http://readbook.ddns.net/?p=65',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(66,1,'2019-05-01 10:28:46','2019-05-01 08:28:46','<!-- wp:html -->\n<p>This website was created for the cours \"Web Information Systems\" given at VUB.<br><br><br></p>\n\n<h3><strong>Development terms:</strong></h3>\n\n<h4>Plugin: read-book</h4>\n\n<p>\n    This plugin contain all custom code develop for this website.<br>\n    He define the following <strong>post</strong>:\n</p>\n<ul>\n    <li><strong>document</strong><br>\n        A document is an article, a book, a conference, ...<br>\n        <strong>Custom Fields:</strong>\n        <ul>\n            <li style=\"list-style-type: circle;\"><strong>text_author</strong><br>Store the author of the document</li>\n            <li style=\"list-style-type: circle;\"><strong>text_google_link</strong><br>Store the link (or the error) of the Google Book information (!= API)</li>\n            <li style=\"list-style-type: circle;\"><strong>text_img</strong><br>URL to an image of the book (fetch by Google API)</li>\n            <li style=\"list-style-type: circle;\"><strong>text_isbn_issn</strong> (optional)<br>ISBN os ISSN of the document</li>\n            <li style=\"list-style-type: circle;\"><strong>text_link</strong> (optional)<br>Link to download the document</li>\n        </ul>\n        <br>\n        <strong>Taxonomy:</strong>\n        <ul>\n            <li style=\"list-style-type: square;\"><strong>DocumentTypes</strong></li>\n            <li style=\"list-style-type: square;\"><strong>Theme</strong> (multiple)</li>\n        </ul>\n        <br>\n    </li>\n    <li><strong>document_point</strong><br>\n        Each document could have different relevant point. document_point is one relevant point.<br>\n        <strong>Custom Fields:</strong>\n        <ul>\n            <li style=\"list-style-type: circle;\"><strong>document_parent</strong><br>The ID of the parent document</li>\n            <li style=\"list-style-type: circle;\"><strong>category</strong> (multiple)<br>Categorize the document point (Official, Summary...)</li>\n            <li style=\"list-style-type: circle;\"><strong>point_approved</strong> (default: 0)<br>Boolean to see if this point is approuved or not</li>\n            <li style=\"list-style-type: circle;\"><strong>was_request</strong> (default: 0)<br>Boolean to know if it was a request or not</li>\n        </ul>\n        <b>Remark:</b> A \'document_point\' have always a \'document\' in parent.\n        <br>\n        <br>\n    </li>\n    <li><strong>point_request</strong><br>\n        Request to develop a relevant point for a specific document.<br>\n        <strong>Custom Fields:</strong>\n        <ul>\n            <li style=\"list-style-type: circle;\"><strong>document_parent</strong><br>The ID of the parent document</li>\n            <li style=\"list-style-type: circle;\"><strong>category</strong> (multiple)<br>Categorize the document point (Official, Summary...)</li>\n        </ul>\n        <br>\n        <strong>Taxonomy:</strong>\n        <ul>\n            <li style=\"list-style-type: square;\"><strong>Skills</strong></li>\n        </ul>\n        <br>\n        <b>Remark:</b> A \'point_request\' have always a \'document\' in parent.\n        <br>\n        <br>\n    </li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3><strong>TODO List</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n    <li><b><span style=\"color: green;\">DONE</span></b> Allow to update document_point</li>\n    <li><b><span style=\"color: green;\">DONE</span></b> [Design] Adapt theme to not use fifu</li>\n    <li>Automaticaly fetch more information about book with Google API</li>\n    <li><b><span style=\"color: green;\">DONE</span></b> Add the possibility to search for a point of interest for a specific book and his custom fields</li>\n    <li><b><span style=\"color: green;\">DONE</span></b> Dynamic search (no redirection to another page) to find point of interest of a book</li>\n    <li>[Design] Display correctly note/rank of a comment</li>\n    <li><b><span style=\"color: green;\">DONE</span></b> Order comment of a point by his note</li>\n    <li><b><span style=\"color: green;\">DONE</span></b> Order point of interest of document by his note</li>\n    <li><b><span style=\"color: green;\">DONE</span></b> Publication -&gt; link to document != date of post</li>\n    <li>[Design] Enhance display of research result</li>\n    <li><b><span style=\"color: green;\">DONE</span></b> Approuved system for document_point</li>\n    <li><b><span style=\"color: green;\">DONE</span></b> Give money when your post is approuved</li>\n    <li><b><span style=\"color: green;\">DONE</span></b> Give money when you have a good comment on your document_point</li>\n    <li><b><span style=\"color: green;\">DONE</span></b> Give money when you comment receive 5 like</li>\n    <li><b><span style=\"color: green;\">DONE</span></b> Possibility to ask point_request</li>\n    <li><b><span style=\"color: green;\">DONE</span></b> Display all point_request linked to a document</li>\n    <li><b><span style=\"color: green;\">DONE</span></b> Give more point to the person which compleet a point_request</li>\n    <li><b><span style=\"color: green;\">DONE</span></b> Doesn\'t allow to comment own post</li>\n    <li><b><span style=\"color: green;\">DONE</span></b> Doesn\'t allow to note own comment</li>\n    <li><b><span style=\"color: green;\">DONE</span></b> Suggest existing category when we create a new point of interest</li>\n    <li>[Design] Display category of a document_point on the page describing it</li>\n    <li>[Design] Display correctly approuved document_point</li>\n    <li>[Design] Display button to navigate easily on \"document\" page</li>\n    <li>Possibility to have all book of a specific author (custom research)</li>\n    <li>For the auto complete a CSS file is mandatory. Currently he is add at the beginning. Must be fix</li>\n    <li><b><span style=\"color: green;\">DONE</span></b> Possibilty to request skills, sort it and search</li>\n    <li>Implement \"first published on\" for a book</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3><strong>Document Point approuved</strong></h3>\n<p>\nA document_point is considered approved when it has more than 5 comments forming a score greater or equal to 3/5.\n</p>\n\n<h3><strong>Extra dev</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n    <li>Use control number in ISBN (last number)</li>\n    <li>Possibility to add reward on a point_request that will be win by the user wich compleet it</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n<h3><strong>Open question to continue development:</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n    <li>User could add custom Theme (linked to a Book) ?<br>\n    <b>No</b></li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3><strong>Money:</strong></h3>\n<p>You have different way to win money</p>\n<ul>\n    <li>When your document_point is approuved (-&gt; 1€)</li>\n    <li>When your document_point is approuved and reply to a specific user ask (-&gt; previous + 0.5 €)</li>\n    <li>When your comment have enought like (5 likes) (-&gt; 0.25 €)</li>\n    <li>When your receive a positive comment on a approuved message (-&gt; 0.1 €)</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n<h3><strong>General remark:</strong></h3>\n\n<ul>\n    <li>Possibility to use only GoogleAPI Books and not store book information: the problem is the limiation of request.</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- /wp:html -->','About us','','publish','closed','closed','','about-us','','','2019-05-21 14:57:53','2019-05-21 12:57:53','',0,'http://readbook.ddns.net/?page_id=66',0,'page','',0),(67,1,'2019-05-01 10:28:46','2019-05-01 08:28:46',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','67','','','2019-05-01 18:39:26','2019-05-01 16:39:26','',0,'http://readbook.ddns.net/2019/05/01/67/',4,'nav_menu_item','',0),(68,1,'2019-05-01 10:28:46','2019-05-01 08:28:46','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This website was created for the cours \"Web Information Systems\" given at VUS.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','About us','','inherit','closed','closed','','66-revision-v1','','','2019-05